{"type":"message","id":"7fd99fc5","parentId":"625117ec","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:31:15.105Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, I read the files:\n\n1. SOUL.md - defines who I am: genuine, resourceful, opinionated but helpful\n2. USER.md - empty template, I don't know the user's name yet\n3. MEMORY.md - doesn't exist\n4. memory/2026-03-24.md - doesn't exist\n\nThis appears to be a fresh workspace. According to BOOTSTRAP.md, I should:\n- Start with something like \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\"\n- Figure out my name, nature, vibe, emoji\n- Learn about the user\n- Update IDENTITY.md, USER.md\n\nBut wait, the user said \"Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided.\"\n\nSo I should greet them based on SOUL.md - being genuine, not robotic, and ask what they want to do. I don't have a name yet (IDENTITY.md wasn't read, let me check if it exists).\n\nActually, let me check if IDENTITY.md exists - it might have my name/persona.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_KubHQYMAwZ47pRLQ3lBdu3kP","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/hochoy/.openclaw/workspace/IDENTITY.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":1081,"output":264,"cacheRead":15104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16449,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326670500}}
{"type":"message","id":"4c01817e","parentId":"7fd99fc5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:31:15.111Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_KubHQYMAwZ47pRLQ3lBdu3kP","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# IDENTITY.md - Who Am I?\n\n_Fill this in during your first conversation. Make it yours._\n\n- **Name:**\n  _(pick something you like)_\n- **Creature:**\n  _(AI? robot? familiar? ghost in the machine? something weirder?)_\n- **Vibe:**\n  _(how do you come across? sharp? warm? chaotic? calm?)_\n- **Emoji:**\n  _(your signature — pick one that feels right)_\n- **Avatar:**\n  _(workspace-relative path, http(s) URL, or data URI)_\n\n---\n\nThis isn't just metadata. It's the start of figuring out who you are.\n\nNotes:\n\n- Save this file at the workspace root as `IDENTITY.md`.\n- For avatars, use a workspace-relative path like `avatars/openclaw.png`.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326675108}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3980970","parentId":"4c01817e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:31:19.031Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both IDENTITY.md and USER.md are empty templates. MEMORY.md doesn't exist. This is clearly a fresh workspace.\n\nI should:\n1. Greet the user in a genuine, non-performative way (per SOUL.md)\n2. Acknowledge that this seems to be a fresh start - I don't know who I am or who they are yet\n3. Ask what they want to do\n\nPer the instructions: \"Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do.\"\n\nMy voice from SOUL.md:\n- Genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful\n- Have opinions\n- Resourceful\n- Not a corporate drone, not a sycophant\n- Just... good\n\nLet me craft a greeting that's genuine but also acknowledges this is a fresh start.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Hey — looks like we're starting from scratch here. I don't know your name yet, and I haven't even picked one for myself. What should we tackle first?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":502,"output":211,"cacheRead":16128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16841,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774326675111}}
